Rating: 3
Great pizza! I made 2 alterations. I used refrigerated pizza dough instead of Boboli, which, I think even the thin crust is too thick. I spread 2/3 cup of salsa over the pizza crust and after all the topping sprinkled another 2/3 cup of salsa over the top. All in all a hardy pizza.

Rating: 3
I enjoyed this pizza! I used frozen bread dough for the pizza crust (much tastier than Boboli) and made fresh salsa (I used three roma tomatoes, two serrano chilis, a thick slice of yellow onion and a small clove of garlic. Put all ingredients in a small skillet over high heat and blacken the skins, turning occasionally. Takes about 5 minutes. Then put everything in a blender with a couple tablespoons of water, 1/4 tsp of salt and 1/8 tsp chicken boullion. Blend well and voila--you have a delicious fresh authentic salsa.) That makes a spicy salsa, so I didn't put any sliced jalepeno on top. I also used a little nonfat plain yogurt at the table and it tasted wonderful! Next time I'll use 3 or 4 tablespoons of black beans too.

