Rating: 4
This is a great recipe to start with if you love to ad lib in the kitchen. I put On The Border salsa down first, then arranged slices of grilled chicken in concentric circles and grated extra sharp cheddar with a flat hand grater right over the pizza - less dishes to wash. Had canned corn onhand, not frozen. Turned out great. For the future, I'll know that salsa makes a great pizza sauce, and you can add just about any southwest ingredients you like - avocado comes to mind...mmmmm!

